their property that they may more perfectly respect it.
		-- G. K. Chesterton, "The Man Who Was Thursday"


Critic, n.:
	A person who boasts himself hard to please because nobody tries
	to please him.
		-- Ambrose Bierce, "The Devil's Dictionary"


